1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:10,000
ArcPredict is a USDC prediction market built for Arc Testnet.

2
00:00:10,000 --> 00:00:23,000
Users take a view on real outcomes while the app keeps settlement rules visible.

3
00:00:23,000 --> 00:00:39,000
The crypto board uses Pyth-backed price deadlines for BTC, ETH, and SOL markets.

4
00:00:39,000 --> 00:00:54,000
Each card shows the question, deadline, pool split, liquidity, and user position.

5
00:00:54,000 --> 00:01:10,000
The World Cup board expands ArcPredict from price markets into event markets.

6
00:01:10,000 --> 00:01:27,000
World Cup markets support home win, draw, away win, spreads, and winner outcomes.

7
00:01:27,000 --> 00:01:42,000
Crypto keeps PredictionMarket and Pyth. Events use EventMarket and AdminEventOracle.

8
00:01:42,000 --> 00:01:55,000
The MVP oracle uses a result proposal plus a 72-hour dispute window.

9
00:01:55,000 --> 00:02:00,000
One interface for markets people can understand, trade, and settle on-chain.
